Garlic Parmesan Pasta (No Cream)
Ingredients (2 servings):

200g pasta

2 tablespoons butter

3 cloves garlic (minced)

½ cup grated Parmesan cheese

½ cup pasta water (from boiling the pasta)

Salt & black pepper

Optional: chili flakes, parsley

Instructions:
1. Cook the pasta

Boil salted water.

Cook pasta until al dente.

Save ½ cup of pasta water, then drain.

2. Make the sauce

Melt butter in a pan.

Add garlic and cook for 30 seconds.

Add Parmesan cheese and a bit of pasta water.

Stir until it becomes a light, creamy sauce (add more water if needed).

3. Combine

Add pasta to the sauce.

Season with salt, pepper, chili flakes.

Mix well.

4. Serve

Top with extra Parmesan and parsley.
